The paper discusses Scientometrics and Bibliometrics indicators for evaluating the scientific impact of individuals, institutions, colleges, universities, and research teams. These indicators are commonly used in the field of Computer Science, particularly in sub-categories such as Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
